 Aerial photo shows a herd of camels in Kubuqi Desert, north China's Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region, Nov. 29, 2021. (Photo by Wang Zheng/Xinhua) HOHHOT, Nov. 30 (Xinhua) -- Kubuqi Desert, China's seventh-largest desert, lies within Inner Mongolia in northern China. A series of ecological projects have been launched in recent years to curb desertification in the region. Visitors now can have fun riding camels in the desert.  Aerial photo shows a herd of camels in Kubuqi Desert, north China's Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region, Nov. 29, 2021. (Photo by Wang Zheng/Xinhua)  Aerial photo shows a herd of camels in Kubuqi Desert, north China's Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region, Nov. 29, 2021. (Photo by Wang Zheng/Xinhua)